        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Annual household final consumption expenditure by purpose (COICOP 2018)</common:Name>
        <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Dépenses annuelles de consommation finale des ménages (COICOP 2018)</common:Name>
        <common:Description xml:lang="en">This table presents the final consumption expenditure of households broken down by the Classification of Individual Consumption According to Purpose (COICOP 2018). The totals are for all final consumption expenditure in the domestic economy, whether by residents or non-residents.<br><br>For countries for which data on Annual household final consumption expenditure by purpose are not yet available according to the COICOP 2018 classification, statistics can be found in this dataset:<a href="https://data-explorer.oecd.org/vis?fs%5b0%5d=Topic%2C1%7CEconomy%23ECO%23%7CNational%20accounts%23ECO_NAD%23&fs%5b1%5d=Topic%2C2%7CEconomy%23ECO%23%7CNational%20accounts%23ECO_NAD%23%7CGDP%20and%20non-financial%20accounts%23ECO_NAD_GNF%23&pg=0&fc=Topic&snb=88&df%5bds%5d=dsDisseminateFinalDMZ&df%5bid%5d=DSD_NAMAIN10%40DF_TABLE5_T501&df%5bag%5d=OECD.SDD.NAD&df%5bvs%5d=1.0&dq=A.AUT.S14......XDC.V..&lom=LASTNPERIODS&lo=5&to%5bTIME_PERIOD%5d=false">Annual household final consumption expenditure by purpose (COICOP)</a><br><br>
The COICOP provides detailed breakdowns, so the presentation is on a country-by-country basis and users are recommended to select one country (or area) at a time in the ‘Reference area’ filter. However, it is also possible to select a small number of expenditure categories in the ‘Expenditure’ filter to compare results for several countries.<br><br>
Data is presented for each country in national currency as well as in euros for the European Union and the euro area. The information is presented in current prices, but users can select chain linked volumes and previous year prices using the ‘Price base’ filter.

<br> See ANA Changes for information on changes in methodology:  <a href="https://stats.oecd.org/wbos/fileview2.aspx?IDFile=e81c82e7-ad8b-4ab9-8b4c-8c3e1e104c9b">ANA Changes</a> <br>
Explore also the GDP and non-financial accounts webpage: <a href="https://www.oecd.org/en/data/datasets/gdp-and-non-financial-accounts.html">GDP and non-financial accounts webpage</a><br>OECD statistics contact: <a href="mailto:STAT.Contact@oecd.org">STAT.Contact@oecd.org</a></common:Description>
        <common:Description xml:lang="fr">Ce tableau présente les dépenses de consommation finale des ménages ventilées selon la Classification des fonctions de consommation des ménages  (COICOP 2018). Les totaux concernent toutes les dépenses de consommation finale dans l’économie nationale, qu’elles soient effectuées par des résidents ou des non-résidents. <br><br>

La COICOP fournit des ventilations détaillées, la présentation se fait donc pays par pays et il est recommandé aux utilisateurs de sélectionner un pays (ou une zone) à la fois dans le filtre « Zone de référence ». Cependant, il est également possible de sélectionner un petit nombre de catégories de dépenses dans le filtre « Dépenses » pour comparer les résultats de plusieurs pays. <br><br>Pour les pays pour lesquels les données sur les dépenses annuelles de consommation finale des ménages ne sont pas encore disponibles selon la classification COICOP 2018, les statistiques peuvent être trouvées dans l'ensemble de données: <a href="https://data-explorer.oecd.org/vis?pg=0&snb=88&df%5bds%5d=dsDisseminateFinalDMZ&df%5bid%5d=DSD_NAMAIN10%40DF_TABLE5_T501&df%5bag%5d=OECD.SDD.NAD&df%5bvs%5d=1.0&dq=A.AUT.S14......XDC.V..&lom=LASTNPERIODS&lo=5&to%5bTIME_PERIOD%5d=false&ly%5bcl%5d=TIME_PERIOD&ly%5brw%5d=COMBINED_UNIT_MEASURE%2CEXPENDITURE&lc=fr">Dépenses annuelles de consommation finale des ménages (COICOP)</a><br><br>

Les données sont présentées pour chaque pays en monnaie nationale ainsi qu'en euros pour l'Union européenne et la zone euro. Les informations sont présentées en prix courants, mais les utilisateurs peuvent sélectionner les volumes chaînés et les prix de l'année précédente à l'aide du filtre « Type de prix ». <br> <br>

<br> Voir Modifications ANA pour plus d'informations sur les changements de méthodologie : <a href="https://stats.oecd.org/wbos/fileview2.aspx?IDFile=e81c82e7-ad8b-4ab9-8b4c-8c3e1e104c9b">Changements ANA< /a> <br>
Explorez également la page Web des comptes nationaux de l'OCDE : <a href="https://www.oecd.org/sdd/na/">Page Web des comptes nationaux</a><br>Contact pour les statistiques de l'OCDE : <a href="mailto : STAT.Contact@oecd.org">STAT.Contact@oecd.org</a</common:Description>

      <structure:Codelist id="CL_CONF_STATUS" agencyID="SDMX" version="1.2" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Confidentiality Status</common:Name>
        <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Statut de confidentialité</common:Name>
        <structure:Code id="F">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Free (free for publication)</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Libre (libre pour publication)</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used for observations without any special sensitivity considerations and which can thus be freely shared. Usually, source organisations provide information and guidance on general requirements for re-dissemination  (like mentioning the source) either on their websites or in their paper publications. In some institutional environments the term "unclassified" is used in a sense that still denotes implied restrictions in the circulation of information. If this is the case, the organisations concerned may probably consider that "free" (value F) is not the appropriate tag for this kind of "unclassified" category and that "Not for publication, restricted for internal use only" (value N) may be more appropriate.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="N">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Not for publication, restricted for internal use only</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Non destiné à la publication, réservé à un usage interne uniquement</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used to denote observations that are restricted for internal use only within organisations. This code may be accompanied with an additional observation-level attribute: CONF_REDIST which defines the secondary recipient(s) to whom the sender allows the primary recipient to forward confidential data.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="C">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Confidential statistical information</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Information statistique confidentielle</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Confidential statistical information (primary confidentiality) due to identifiable respondents. Measures also should be taken to prevent not only direct access, but also indirect deduction or calculation by other users and parties, probably by considering and treating additional observations as "confidential" (secondary confidentiality management).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="D">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Secondary confidentiality set by the sender, not for publication</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité secondaire définie par l'expéditeur, non destinée à la publication</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used by the sender of the data to flag (beyond the confidential statistical information) additional observations in the dataset so that the receiver knows that he/she should suppress these observations in subsequent stages of processing (especially dissemination) in order to prevent third parties to indirectly deduct the observations that are genuinely flagged with "C".</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="S">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Secondary confidentiality set and managed by the receiver, not for publication</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité secondaire définie et gérée par le destinataire, pas pour publication</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">If senders do not manage the secondary confidentiality in their data and/or there are also other countries' data involved (with the intention to eventually compile a regional-wide aggregate that is going to be published), the value "S" is used by the receiver to flag additional suppressed observations (within sender's data and/or within the datasets of other senders) in subsequent stages of processing (especially, dissemination) in order to prevent third parties to indirectly deduct the observations that were genuinely flagged with "C" by the sender.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to small counts</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire en raison des petits comptes</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">A cell is flagged as confidential if less than m units ("too few units") contribute to the total of that cell. The limits of what constitutes "small counts" can vary across statistical domains, countries, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="O">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to dominance by one unit</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire due à la dominance d'une unité</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used when one unit accounts for more than x % of the total of a cell. The value of x can vary across statistical domains or countries, be influenced by legislation, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="T">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to dominance by two units</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire due à la dominance de deux unités</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used when two units account for more than x % of the total of a cell. The value of x can vary across statistical domains or countries, be influenced by legislation, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="G">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to dominance by one or two units</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire due à la dominance d'une ou deux unités</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used when one or two units account(s) for more than x % of the total of a cell. The value of x can vary across statistical domains or countries, be influenced by legislation, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="M">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to data declared confidential based on other measures of concentration</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire due aux données déclarées confidentielles sur la base d'autres mesures de concentration</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Cells declared confidential using mathematical definitions of sensitive cells, e.g. p-percent, p/q or (n,k) rules.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="E">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Not for publication, restricted for internal use only (equivalent to the code N) until the embargo time elapses; Free for publication (equivalent to the code F) after the embargo time elapses.</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Non destiné à la publication, réservé à un usage interne uniquement (équivalent au code N) jusqu'à l'expiration du délai d'embargo ; Libre de publication (équivalent au code F) après l'expiration du délai d'embargo.</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used for embargoed data. The embargo time has to be specified in the EMBARGO_TIME attribute. This code may be accompanied with an additional observation-level attribute: CONF_REDIST which defines the secondary recipient(s) to whom the sender allows the primary recipient to forward confidential data.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
      </structure:Codelist>

More information about this code list and SDMX code lists in general (e.g. list of generic codes for expressing general concepts like "Total", "Unknown", etc.; syntaxes for the creation of further codes; general guidelines for the creation of SDMX code lists) can be found at this address: https://sdmx.org/?page_id=4345.</common:Description>

      <structure:Codelist isPartial="true" id="CL_FREQ" agencyID="SDMX" version="2.1" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Code list for concept "Frequency"</common:Name>
        <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Codelist pour le concept "Fréquence"</common:Name>
        <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code list provides a set of values indicating
					the "frequency" of the data (e.g. weekly, monthly, quarterly). The concept
					"frequency" may refer to various stages in the production process, e.g. data
					collection or data dissemination. For example, a time series could be
					disseminated at annual frequency but the underlying data are compiled monthly.
					The code list is applicable for all different uses of
					"frequency".</common:Description>
        <common:Description xml:lang="fr">Cette liste de codes fournit un ensemble de valeurs
					indiquant la "fréquence" des données (par exemple, hebdomadaire, mensuelle,
					trimestrielle). Le concept de "fréquence" peut faire référence à différentes
					étapes du processus de production, par ex. collecte ou diffusion de données. Par
					exemple, une série chronologique pourrait être diffusée à une fréquence
					annuelle, mais les données sous-jacentes sont compilées mensuellement. La liste
					de codes est applicable pour toutes les différentes utilisations de
					"fréquence".</common:Description>
        <structure:Code id="A">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Annual</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Annuelle</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every year</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
      </structure:Codelist>
      <structure:Codelist id="CL_OBS_STATUS" agencyID="SDMX" version="2.2" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Observation Status</common:Name>
        <structure:Code id="A">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Normal value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used as default value if no value is provided or when no special coded qualification is assumed. Usually, it can be assumed that the source agency assigns sufficient confidence to the provided observation and/or the value is not expected to be dramatically revised.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="B">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Time series break</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Observations are characterised as such when different content exists or a different methodology has been applied to this observation as compared with the preceding one (the one given for the previous period).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="D">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Definition differs</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used to indicate slight deviations from the established methodology (footnote-type information); these divergences do not imply a break in time series.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="E">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Estimated value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Observation obtained through an estimation methodology (e.g. to produce back-casts) or based on the use of a limited amount of data or ad hoc sampling and through additional calculations (e.g. to produce a value at an early stage of the production stage while not all data are available). It may also be used in case of experimental data (e.g. in the context of a pilot ahead of a full scale production process) or in case of data of (anticipated/assessed) low quality. If needed, additional information can be provided through free text using the COMMENT_OBS attribute at the observation level or at a higher level. This code is to be used when the estimation is done by a sender agency. When the imputation is carried out by a receiver agency in order to replace or fill gaps in reported data series, the flag to use is I "Value imputed by a receiving agency".</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="F">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Forecast value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Value deemed to assess the magnitude which a quantity will assume at some future point of time (as distinct from "estimated value" which attempts to assess the magnitude of an already existent quantity).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="G">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Experimental value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Data collected on the basis of definitions or (alternative) collection methods under development. Data not of guaranteed quality as normally expected from provider.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="I">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Value imputed by a receiving agency</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Observation imputed by a receiving agency to replace or fill gaps in reported data series. This code is intended to cover all cases where a receiving agency publishes data about a sending agency that do not come from an official source in the sender agency's reporting framework. When the estimation is done by the sender agency, the flag to use is E "Estimated value".</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="K">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Data included in another category</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code is used when data for a given category are missing and are included in another category, sub-total or total. Generally where code "K" is used there should be a corresponding code "W - Includes data from another category" assigned to the over-covered category. Implementers and data reporters should use the COMMENT_OBS observation-level attribute to specify under which category the data are included.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="W">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Includes data from another category</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code is used when data include another category, or go beyond the scope of the data collection and are therefore over-covered. Generally, where code "W" is used there should be a corresponding code "K - Data included in another category" assigned to the category which is under-covered. Implementers and data reporters should use the COMMENT_OBS observation-level attribute to specify which additional data are included.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="O">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code is to be used when no breakdown is made between the reasons why data are missing. Data can be missing due to many reasons: data cannot exist, data exist but are not collected (e.g. because they are below a certain threshold or subject to a derogation clause), data are unreliable, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="M">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value; data cannot exist</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used to denote empty cells resulting from the impossibility to collect a statistical value (e.g. a particular education level or type of institution may be not applicable to a given country's education system).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="P">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Provisional value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">An observation is characterised as "provisional" when the source agency - while it bases its calculations on its standard production methodology - considers that the data, almost certainly, are expected to be revised.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="S">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strike and other special events</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Special circumstances (e.g. strike) affecting the observation or causing a missing value.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="L">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value; data exist but were not collected</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used, for example, when some data are not reported/disseminated because they are below a certain threshold.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="H">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value; holiday or weekend</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used in some daily data flows.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="Q">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value; suppressed</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used, for example, when data are suppressed due to statistical confidentiality considerations.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="J">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Derogation</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Clause in an agreement (e.g. legal act, gentlemen's agreement) stating that some provisions in the agreement are not to be implemented by designated parties; these derogations may affect the observation or cause a missing value. In general, derogations are limited in time.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="N">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Not significant</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used to indicate a value which is not a "real" zero (e.g. a result of 0.0004 rounded to zero).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="U">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Low reliability</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">This indicates existing observations, but for which the user should also be aware of the low quality assigned.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="V">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Unvalidated value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Observation as received from the respondent without further evaluation of data quality.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
      </structure:Codelist>
      <structure:Codelist id="CL_UNIT_MULT" agencyID="SDMX" version="1.1" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Unit Multiplier</common:Name>
        <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code list provides code values for indicating the magnitude in the units of measurement. More information about this code list and SDMX code lists in general (e.g. list of generic codes for expressing general concepts like "Total", "Unknown", etc.;
          syntaxes for the creation of further codes; general guidelines for the creation of SDMX code lists) can be found at this address: https://sdmx.org/?page_id=4345.</common:Description>

        <structure:Code id="5">

        <structure:Code id="8">

        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="9">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Billions</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of nine (10^9)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="10">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Tens of billions</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of ten (10^10)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="11">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Hundreds of billions</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of eleven (10^11)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="12">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Trillions</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of twelve (10^12)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="13">

          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of thirteen (10^13)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="14">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Hundreds of trillions</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of fourteen (10^14)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="15">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Quadrillions</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of fifteen (10^15)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="-1">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Tenths</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of minus one (10^-1)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="-2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Hundredths</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of minus two (10^-2)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="-3">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Thousandths</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">In scientific notation, expressed as ten raised to the power of minus three (10^-3)</common:Description>
